VI would be incredibly surprised if you even need to load all your information in memory
p6036
aVI say this because, just as one example, I'm working on a Web app at the moment that (for various reasons) loads thousands of records on many pages
p6037
aVThis is PHP + MySQL
p6038
aVAnd even so it can do it and render a page in well under 100ms
p6039
aVBefore you go down this route make sure that you have to
p6040
aVFirst make your database as performant as possible
p6041
aVNow obviously this includes things like having appropriate indexes and tuning your database but even though are putting the horse before the cart
p6042
aVFirst and foremost you need to make sure you have a good relational data model: one that lends itself to performant queries
p6043
aVThis is as much art as it is science
p6044
aVAlso, you may like NHibernate but ORMs are not always the best choice
p6045
aVThere are some corner cases, for example, that hand-coded SQL will be vastly superior in
p6046
aVNow assuming you have a good data model and assuming you've then optimized your indexes and database parameters and then you've properly configured NHibernate, then and only then should you consider storing data in memory if and only if performance is still an issue
p6047
aVTo put this in perspective, the only times I've needed to do this are on systems that need to perform millions of transactions per day
p6048
aVOne reason to avoid in-memory caching is because it adds a lot of complexity
p6049
aVYou have to deal with issues like cache expiry, independent updates to the underlying data store, whether you use synchronous or asynchronous updates, how you give the client a consistent (if not up-to-date) view of your data, how you deal with failover and replication and so on
p6050
aVThere is a huge complexity cost to be paid
p6051
aVAssuming you've done all the above and you still need it, it sounds to me like what you need is a cache or grid solution
p6052
aVHere is an overview of Java grid/cluster solutions but many of them (eg Coherence, memcached) apply to
p6053
aVNet as well
