aVBut still PHP scripts are basically transient
p7274
aVSession information is (normally) file based and mutually exclusive (session_start() blocks other scripts accessing the same user session until session_commit() or the script finishes) whereas that's not the case in ASP
p7275
aVNET
p7276
aVAside from session data, it's fairly easy (and normal) to have objects that live within the application context in ASP
p7277
aVNET (or Java for that matter, which ASP
p7278
