p17746
aVA common component to use with memcache\u2014at least in the PHP world\u2014is beanstalkd as a distributed work queue processor
p17747
aVIn this scenario you can fire off an "update cache" request as a unit of work
p17748
aVIf you are doing an operation on the cache entry that uses the existing value as an input or in some other way would introduce a race condition if get-then-update weren't an atomic operation, an alternative is to create a unit of work that includes the old value and the new value
p17749
aVThat way, whatever process handles the updates can invalidate or otherwise handle those situations where the current value isn't the expected value
p17750
aVIncrementing and decrementing are handled by the memcached interface so if your accesses are of that type (or can be reduced to that kind of operation) then that solves the problem as well
