VGenerally speaking with databases you rarely delete anything
p21595
aVYou can mark it as deleted but generally speaking you keep it in your database at least for a time
p21596
aVThere are many reasons for this
p21597
aVSome of them are legal
p21598
aVYou may have requirements ot keep data for a given period
p21599
aVSome of them are technical
p21600
aVSometimes its just a safeguard
p21601
aVYou may need to restore the information
p21602
aVThe user may request their account is reopened or it may have been locked due to spamming but that was because the account had been compromised and has now been restored
p21603
aVOld data may be deleted or archived but this may take months or even years
p21604
aVPersonally I just give relevant data a status column (eg 1 = active, 0 = deleted) and then just change the status rather than delete it 99% of the time
p21605
aVData integrity is another issue here
p21606
aVLet me give you an example
p21607
aVAssume you have two entities:
p21608
aVYou want to delete a particular User
p21609
aVWhat do you do about messages they've sent and received
p21610
aVThose messages will appear in someone else's inbox or sent items so you can't delete them
p21611
aVDo you set the relevant field in Message to NULL
p21612
aVThat doesn't make a lot of sense either because that message did come from (or go to) somebody, even if they aren't active anymore
p21613
aVYou're better off just marking that user as deleted and keeping them around
p21614
aVIt makes this and similar situations much easier to deal with
p21615
aVYou also mention forum threads and so on
p21616
aVYou can't delete those either (unless there are other reasons to do so such as spam or abuse) because they're content that is related to other content (eg forum messages that have been replied to)
p21617
aVThe only data you can safely and reasonably delete is child data
p21618
aVThis is really the difference between aggregation and composition
p21619
aVThe User and message relationship above is aggregation
p21620
aVAn example of composition is House and Room
p21621
aVYou delete a House and all the rooms go to
p21622
aVRooms cannot exist without a House
p21623
aVThis is composition or, in entity relationship terms, a parent-child relationship
p21624
aVBut you'll find more instances of aggregation than composition (in my experience) so the question becomes: what do you do with that data
p21625
aVIt's really hard to erase all traces of someone without deleting things you shouldn't
p21626
aVJust mark them as deleted, locked or inactive and deal with it that way
