aVLastly you have the functional languages: Haskell, OCaml, Scheme/Lisp, Clojure, F#, etc
p36237
aVThese think about all problems in a very different way and are worth learning at some point but again it comes down to what you want to learn: functional programming or data structures
p36238
aVI'd stick to learning one thing at a time rather than confusing the issue
p36239
aVIf you do learn a functional language at some point (which I would recommend), Haskell is a safe and fine choice
